                <h1>Harriet Tubman: The Brave Conductor of Freedom</h1>
                <p>Harriet Tubman, born into slavery in 1822, became a legendary figure in the fight for freedom. After escaping herself, she risked her life repeatedly to lead hundreds of enslaved people to safety via the Underground Railroad. Her bravery and tireless efforts as a suffragist and abolitionist make her an enduring symbol of courage and resilience.</p>
